Pink coral, cedar trees, and various fish species are set to receive increased protection, as per a UN agency.
Overexploitation threatens Brazilian lobsters and sawfish, prompting calls for trade halts.
The EU seeks permits for European eels and spiny dogfish to manage fisheries.
Climate change poses a severe threat to coral reefs, impacting biodiversity.
Efforts to regulate coral trade aim to ensure sustainability and prevent further depletion.
Conservation initiatives, including coral restoration projects and tourism partnerships, are crucial for protecting fragile marine ecosystems worldwide.
Awareness and collaboration are key to preserving coral reefs amidst growing environmental challenges.
